The National Association ofSecurities Dealers Inc. denied Kirk Knapp's application tobecome a registered member of the firm.    NASD's board of governors said it denied the application ofKnapp to become registered with K.A. Knapp and Co, located inGrand Rapids, Mich. The board said it based its decision on twostatutory disqualifications.    In the first case, the board said it found Knapp failed tomaintain rquired net capital, filed inaccurate Focus Part 1reports and inaccurately calculated the amount required to beon deposit in the Special Reserve Account.    The second case involved Knapp being enjoined fromviolations of sections of the Securities Exchange Act, the NASDsaid. Reuter&#3;